<doc id="83121" url="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=83121" title="Thaumas">
Thaumas

In Greek mythology, Thaumas (; Θαύμας; "gen".: Θαύμαντος; folk etymology "wonder") was a sea god, son of Pontus and Gaia. He married an Oceanid, Electra (or Ozomene). The children of Thaumas and Electra were the Harpies and Iris, the goddess of rainbows and a messenger of the gods; according to some, also Arke.
Poseidon overthrew him and became the new sea god.
Thaumas was also the name of a centaur.

