The program's aim is to promote an international network with European universities and Indian Universities.
Research.
Research at Ecole centrale Nantes is carried out in highly competitive laboratories. Theses labs are internationally recognized, as collaborate with a lot of firms.
"Ecole centrale de Nantes" hosts 4 laboratories, recognized as CNRS laboratories:
Robotics, Image, Signal et Automatics, Mechanical and Productive Systems, Electronic Systems, Telecom and Radar
Hydrodynamics and Ocean Engineering, Computational Fluid Dynamics, Dynamics of Inhabited Atmosphere, Internal Combustion Engines
Metallic and Composites Assemblies, Computational Mechanics, Polymers, Dynamics and Processing Technology
Non linear PDE, Probability statistic..
"Ecole Centrale de Nantes" has also launched the "Chaire Fondation EADS Centrale Nantes" on September 9, 19th, a highly skilled research center: Advanced Modeling of Composites Manufacturing Processes
